sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1039026
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Bxb1 Invertible Medium Strength Promoter Switch Test Construct
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Bxb1 invertible promoter switch (BBa_K1039002) in PB state with gfp gene (BBa_K1039015) on the prefix side of the switch and rfp gene (BBa_J04450) on the suffix side. GFP is produced in this state of the switch.
The invertible promoter is strong promoter J23118.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jama Hagi-Yusuf
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The parts were synthesized from BioBasic Inc or from the parts registry

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RBS-RFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RFP, BBa_E1010, with Elowitz RBS, BBa_B0034.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kathy Lam, Danielle Nash
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part was needed for downstream applications. There can be no expression of a reporter without a ribosome binding site.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BS2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The medium strength constitutive promoter J23111 complementary sequence is flanked by the Bxb1 attP and the complementary sequence of the Bxb1 attB site. In the default state the promoter directs transcription on the negative sense strand towards the attP site. In the presence of the Bxb1 integrase the attP and attB sites are recombined and the promoter is directing transcription to the sense strand towards the attB site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Aaron Bender
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Ghosh, P., Kim, A. I. & Hatfull, G. F. (2003). The orientation of mycobacteriophage Bxb1 integration is solely dependent on the central dinucleotide of attP and attB. Mol Cell 12, 1101-1111.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The transcriptional terminator J61048 was included to ensure transcription only proceeds in the expected direction. Spacer regions were added adopted from ... NheI site ...

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1039015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is a gfp sequence with the ORF identical to the sequence of (BBa_E0040), but it is oriented opposite to the BioBrick convention. That is, it is read from suffix to prefix, and the coding strand is the opposite strand compared to most BioBricks. This can be expressed from a similarly ???inverted??? promoter.
This can be used with invertible promoter switches, such as BBa_K1039008, BBa_K1039009, BBa_K1039001 and BBa_K1039002 which require the genes on either side of the switch to have opposite coding strands.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jama Hagi-Yusuf
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequenced was synthesized by BioBasic Inc.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The coding sequence is read from suffix to prefix, rather than prefix to suffix.
